<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="472" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1180,1674]" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,339,1468,1493]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">Distribution</emphasis>
. Representatives of this genus have been collected in the following ecoregions of 
<collectingCountry box="[1333,1432,1469,1494]" name="Namibia" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">Namibia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,302,1505,1530]" name="Mozambique" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[317,465,1505,1530]" name="South Africa" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">
<collectingRegion box="[317,382,1505,1530]" country="Tanzania" name="Kusini Unguja" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">South</collectingRegion>
Africa
</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[528,648,1505,1530]" name="Zimbabwe" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">Zimbabwe</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[667,740,1505,1530]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1731,1753]" captionTargetBox="[161,1437,844,1704]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1437,844,1710]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 5. Distribution of the species representing Anaxius." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457477/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
): Drakensberg montane grasslands, woodlands, and forests; Highveld grasslands; Kalahari xeric savanna; Southern Africa bushveld; and Southern Miombo woodlands.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1180,1674]" box="[199,1318,1577,1602]" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fahraeus" authorityYear="1870" box="[199,290,1578,1601]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Anaxius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="472" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[199,290,1578,1601]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">Anaxius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recorded from localities distributed between 874 and 1544 meters in elevation (
<figureCitation box="[1236,1304,1577,1602]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1413,1435]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,193,1392]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[150,1436,193,1392]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 6. Distribution of the genus Anaxius in the Limpopo Province." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457479/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="472" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1180,1674]" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,253,1614,1637]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">Note</emphasis>
