<taxonomicName authorityName="Fahraeus" authorityYear="1870" box="[668,758,1614,1637]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Anaxius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="472" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[668,758,1614,1637]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">Anaxius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens were studied. Among this number a total of three females was identified. Because of this the following key includes only the male morphology.
</paragraph>
